Newsroom | Vail Resorts Corporate
































Vail Resorts Makes an Epic Promise – Commits to Zero Net Operating Footprint by 2030
Vail Resorts, Inc. (NYSE: MTN) today announced that the Company will aggressively pursue a comprehensive sustainability commitment, called “Epic Promise for a Zero Footprint”. This ambitious undertaking, announced to employees at a companywide event today, commits to zero net emissions by 2030, zero waste to landfill by 2030 and zero net operating impact to forests and habitat.






Vail Resorts Closes Its Acquisition of Stowe Mountain Resort in Vermont, Representing the Company’s First Ski Resort on the East Coast







Epic Discovery Debuts at Breckenridge This Summer
Vail Resorts’ Epic Discovery program encourages “learn through play,” promoting environmental education and forest stewardship with numerous fun experiential activities across three different mountain resorts, Vail Mountain, Breckenridge and Heavenly. The Epic Discovery experience will incorporate extensive environmental and interpretive programming that offers guests a unique opportunity to try new outdoor activities, challenge themselves physically, discover an appreciation for nature and create lasting family memories.






The Great Summer Break has Arrived at Vail Resorts
The Great Summer Break is here and now is the time to lock in the best rates on vacations across Vail Resorts and RockResorts destinations, including Vail, Beaver Creek, Breckenridge, Keystone, Park City, Heavenly, Northstar, Kirkwood and Grand Teton National Park.






Vail Resorts Names Bobby Murphy Vice President and General Manager of Stowe Mountain Resort




















