Glossary

What stars mean

It's important to understand stars usually indicate the facilities available, not the quality of the hotel. Usually, the higher the star, the higher the price.
Functional. Clean, no frills, with minimal facilities.
 More facilities. A telephone, private bathroom and TV.
 More style and comfort. Often have pools in hot climates. 
 Upmarket. Nice dining facilities, pool and public spaces.
Luxury. Pool, gym, interior designed with large public spaces. 
Prestige. Personal concierge services, high-end luxury.

