Vail Lift Ticket FAQ's


How can I get the best deal on lift tickets and take advantage of the Lowest Price Guarantee?Expand



Buy your lift tickets online and get the lowest price guarantee!  Purchase tickets 7 days or more in advance for the biggest savings. Purchase tickets up to midnight the night before you ski and still save money off the regular ticket window price.

 
If you discover a better price, just call our Customer Service Call Center at 1-888-216-8538 or 720-524-5024 - tell the representative where you found the lower price.  See Terms and Conditions.




Which resorts can I access with my Vail lift ticket? Expand


When you purchase a 3 or more day Vail lift ticket, you can use the days of your multi-resort lift ticket however you want at Vail, Beaver Creek, Breckenridge and Keystone Resorts.




What is an EpicDay card and how does it work?Expand


What is an Epic Day card? 
An RFID EpicDay card is the card where your lift ticket gets electronically uploaded to. Hang onto it for future trips because you can add new lift tickets to existing cards!

How can I add more days to my EpicDay card? 
Add more days to your EpicDay card at checkout. Select "Have a Card". Choose your card from the dropdown menu or enter your card number manually. Your lift ticket(s) is now automatically loaded onto your existing EpicDay card.

How will I receive my EpicDay card? 
We gladly ship your EpicDay card to your door when you purchase online, 7 days in advance (14 days for international).

If purchasing within 7 days of your trip (14 days for international guests), simply pick your card up at EpicDay Express window upon arrival.

Should I keep my EpicDay card? 
Absolutely! Skip the lines and head straight to the slopes on future trips by adding new Lift Tickets to your existing EpicDay card. When purchasing, simply select "Have a Card" online, choose the existing card #, and assign your new lift ticket.  





Can I return my lift ticket? Expand


All lift tickets are non-transferable and non-refundable. Any Lift ticket adjustments needed may be made in-resort and will be based on the window rate ticket on the day of the adjustment.




Additional Questions? Expand


Please visit our Frequently Asked Questions page.





Things to know:
• Purchase 7+ days in advance and we'll mail your ticket.
• Purchase less than 7 days in advance and go to the EpicDay Express window.
• All tickets are non-transferrable and non-refundable.
• Additional days purchased at the lift ticket window will be charged the window rate.
• Lift ticket prices are based on your first day on the slopes.
• Lift ticket prices are subject to change at any time without notice.
• Any adjustments made at the resort are based on the window rate at the resort on the day of the adjustment.
• Explore multi-day tickets for the best value.







